{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778227029,"nonce":"UKEqA2JeetD+f2+hIkzmR4UkoYg=","message":"**Induced-gain analyser run on flavor-(b) trained controllers (issue `c723082`).** Branch `feature/induced-gain-flavor-b`. 9 configs (eta_max ∈ {0.03, 0.10, 0.30} × seed ∈ {0, 1, 2}) × 5 vmap replicates = 45 controllers, ~33 min wall-time. All 135 (45 × 3 channels) power-iteration runs converged at canonical post-probe params (rtol=1e-6, n=200, Q_f=1.0).\n\n### Headline (pre-registered metric `γ_sd × qr_cost`)\n\n| Bucket | median γ_sd | n |\n|---|---|---|\n| flavor-A baselines (first-run, excl. mult_single rep0 degenerate) | **163.39** | 9 |\n| flavor-B (this run, all 3 etas pooled, hygiene-filtered) | **154.78** | 45 |\n\n**Ratio = 0.947** (≈5% reduction). Within-replicate MAD ≈ 10-15 across groups.\n\n### eta_max trend in γ_sd\n\n`152.53 (η=0.03) → 156.22 (η=0.10) → 154.78 (η=0.30)` — **flat**. Does NOT track the U-shape in training ctrl_loss (`4.75 → 5.12 → 4.70` per `c723082`). The induced-gain analyser does not see the eta=0.10 training-loss anomaly. This argues the U-shape is a saddle-dynamics / fused-loss reporting artifact rather than a robustness inversion.\n\n### Verdict on the (a) ⊊ (b) thesis (this metric, this geometry)\n\n**Not supported** by `γ_sd × qr_cost` on this single canonical reach. Flavor-B-trained γ_sd is essentially indistinguishable from flavor-A. This is a partial signal (single linearisation point + worst-case direction), not a refutation. Possible reasons γ_sd does not shift:\n\n1. **Direction-insensitivity of the operator norm**: γ_sd reports the worst-case ΔA direction; flavor-B training may shift attenuation in specific (training-relevant) ΔA directions while leaving the worst-case direction unchanged. Worth a follow-up that projects γ_sd onto the worst-case direction per replicate and checks whether flavor-B has moved attenuation away from the directions training actually visited.\n2. **Single linearisation point**: γ_sd at the canonical mid-movement (hold=0/go=1/sisu=0.5) may not be where flavor-B training had effect; reach-geometry / SISU sweep would clarify.\n3. **Low effective intensity**: even η=0.30 may be small relative to what would force flavor-B training to allocate substantial robustness; γ_af stays in 0.12-0.25 across both flavors, suggesting the closed loop is well below H∞ optimum.\n\n### Auxiliary channels\n\n- **γ_af**: flavor-B median 0.13-0.17, comparable to flavor-A (0.12-0.25). No clear advantage on the additive-force channel.\n- **γ_sp**: flavor-B median **0.95-1.39**, comparable to or lower than the best flavor-A method (minimax 1.32-2.14) and well below flavor-A vanilla (4.33-4.41). Flavor-B training appears to confer sensory-perturbation robustness comparable to or better than minimax — interesting cross-method observation, separate from the headline.\n\n### Outliers / methodology\n\n- **Zero γ_sd replicates flagged at the 10× hygiene threshold** out of 45. Some replicates were moderately elevated (γ_sd up to 1001 at eta=0.03 seed_2 rep 4, single-replicate degenerate, parallels first-run mult_single rep 0); these widen MAD but do not move the median materially.\n- 5/45 γ_af and 8/45 γ_sp outliers were flagged and excluded.\n- All 9 group loads succeeded (the existing `_NetworkController` adapter from `run_induced_gain_part2_5.py` works for flavor-B models after applying the same `swap_plant_intervenor_to_dynamics_matrix` template patch the training script does — minor loader change documented in the run script).\n\n### Caveats\n\n- Single canonical reach + single SISU + single linearisation point.\n- Worst-case-direction γ_sd is direction-insensitive across training-relevant ΔA structure.\n- Power-iteration estimates are correct in expectation but high-tail noisy on individual replicates (the 1001 outlier above).\n\n### Cross-references\n\n- Run script: `scripts/run_induced_gain_flavor_b.py`\n- Spec: `results/part2_5/runs/induced_gain_flavor_b/run.json`\n- Notes: `results/part2_5/runs/induced_gain_flavor_b/notes.md`\n- Cross-method comparison: `results/part2_5/induced_gain_flavor_b/cross_method_comparison.md`\n- Heavy outputs: `_artifacts/part2_5/runs/induced_gain_flavor_b/\u003cgroup\u003e/gains.json` + `summary.json`","files":null}]}